1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,500
Monitor,

2
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:01,530
do you want to go to the cinema

3
00:00:01,530 --> 00:00:02,630
with me and Maomao?

4
00:00:03,130 --> 00:00:04,300
I heard that action film

5
00:00:04,300 --> 00:00:05,170
is thrilling and touching.

6
00:00:05,170 --> 00:00:05,870
Don't miss it!

7
00:00:05,870 --> 00:00:07,800
Didn't you agree
to play basketball with us?

8
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:08,840
What basketball?

9
00:00:08,840 --> 00:00:10,140
Why didn't you guys
arrange it ahead of time?

10
00:00:10,140 --> 00:00:11,370
Wait.

11
00:00:11,370 --> 00:00:12,410
Didn't you promise to stay

12
00:00:12,410 --> 00:00:14,410
and decorate the classroom with me?

13
00:00:14,410 --> 00:00:15,240
Go to the cinema!

14
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:15,810
Play basketball!

15
00:00:15,810 --> 00:00:17,080
I bought everything!

16
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:17,780
Go to the cinema!

17
00:00:17,780 --> 00:00:19,080
How about this?

18
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:20,520
I'll decorate the classroom with you

19
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:22,120
from 5:30 p.m. to 6:30 p.m.

20
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:24,120
Then we'll play basketball
from 6:30 p.m. to 7:30 p.m.

21
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:25,410
After that,
I'll go to the cinema with you.

22
00:00:25,410 --> 00:00:26,270
Okay?

23
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:27,770
Of course.

24
00:00:27,820 --> 00:00:29,220
Besides, it's Saturday tomorrow.

25
00:00:29,220 --> 00:00:31,230
We can play all night!

26
00:00:31,230 --> 00:00:34,330
Late-night snacks!

27
00:00:34,330 --> 00:00:35,630
You must be thirsty.

28
00:00:35,630 --> 00:00:37,030
How about I buy you drinks?

29
00:00:37,030 --> 00:00:38,100
Sure.

30
00:00:38,670 --> 00:00:40,530
Thank you, monitor!

31
00:00:40,770 --> 00:00:41,940
You're the best!

32
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:42,800
What movie?

33
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:44,200
What do you want to watch?

34
00:01:08,460 --> 00:01:09,660
Chen Haowei.

35
00:01:10,470 --> 00:01:12,789
I want to go to the cinema
with you tonight.

36
00:01:12,789 --> 00:01:13,930
How did you know?

37
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:16,100
I'm in the same group chat
with Maomao and the others.

38
00:01:16,100 --> 00:01:17,270
But they haven't sent me

39
00:01:17,270 --> 00:01:18,210
the time and place.

40
00:01:18,210 --> 00:01:19,630
I can tell you.

41
00:01:21,270 --> 00:01:22,260
Send me a message.

42
00:01:22,260 --> 00:01:23,190
I'll friend you.

43
00:01:30,610 --> 00:01:31,610
I have a question.

44
00:01:31,830 --> 00:01:34,360
What's the name of that student
in your class?

45
00:01:37,390 --> 00:01:38,900
Just an outcast in our class.

46
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:39,830
He's a weirdo.

47
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:42,780
He always gets the last place in exams,
trying to draw our attention.

48
00:01:42,780 --> 00:01:44,450
So, what's his name?

49
00:01:47,690 --> 00:01:48,490
He Xiangyong.

50
00:01:49,030 --> 00:01:49,930
He Xiangyong.

51
00:01:50,430 --> 00:01:51,000
Thanks.

52
00:01:51,570 --> 00:01:52,610
I'll send you a sticker.

53
00:01:52,610 --> 00:01:53,070
Check it out.

54
00:01:53,070 --> 00:01:53,479
Okay.

55
00:02:46,030 --> 00:02:48,810
[Wishing Upon the Shooting Stars]

56
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:58,520
What exactly did you come to Xingpu Island

57
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,820
to find him for?

58
00:03:02,830 --> 00:03:03,700
Actually...

59
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:04,680
Who did it?

60
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:14,740
Who made this bitter gourd black tea?

61
00:03:16,740 --> 00:03:18,140
You said she came alone.

62
00:03:18,460 --> 00:03:19,420
Who are you?

63
00:03:22,329 --> 00:03:25,250
Only He Xiangyong knows
I drink bitter gourd black tea

64
00:03:25,250 --> 00:03:26,579
when I'm stuck.

65
00:03:26,610 --> 00:03:27,590
How do you know?

66
00:03:34,860 --> 00:03:37,829
Actually, I struggle with anxiety.

67
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:41,079
When I'm anxious, I'm like...

68
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:45,190
And I read in a book once that

69
00:03:45,190 --> 00:03:47,320
bitter gourd black tea
can relieve anxiety,

70
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:49,990
so I decided to make you a cup.

71
00:03:51,530 --> 00:03:52,380
I get you.

72
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:57,570
You're Xixi, right?

73
00:03:58,130 --> 00:03:58,770
Wait...

74
00:04:01,270 --> 00:04:02,330
You're wearing...

75
00:04:02,610 --> 00:04:03,410
What's wrong?

76
00:04:05,010 --> 00:04:06,150
You saw it!

77
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:07,750
Calm down!

78
00:04:08,130 --> 00:04:09,280
No, we didn't see anything!

79
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:10,740
Chen Haowei, listen to me.

80
00:04:11,510 --> 00:04:12,610
Did you just see a grumpy,

81
00:04:12,610 --> 00:04:14,220
angry-looking girl?

82
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,120
I did.

83
00:04:16,540 --> 00:04:17,380
That's right.

84
00:04:17,490 --> 00:04:19,420
Did you see a girl running around

85
00:04:19,420 --> 00:04:21,060
in plaid boxers?

86
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,480
Well, she...

87
00:04:22,510 --> 00:04:23,910
Look at me!

88
00:04:24,450 --> 00:04:25,820
Now, answer my question.

89
00:04:25,820 --> 00:04:28,090
Did you see a messy girl with no makeup

90
00:04:28,110 --> 00:04:30,690
who looks just like Xixi?

91
00:04:32,820 --> 00:04:34,280
No, I didn't!

92
00:04:34,470 --> 00:04:35,170
Great.

93
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:35,810
No!

94
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:37,130
That's good.

95
00:04:39,230 --> 00:04:40,170
I think

96
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,510
Xixi might be hungry when she comes out.

97
00:04:43,380 --> 00:04:44,930
Let's go to the kitchen and see

98
00:04:44,930 --> 00:04:46,080
what we can prepare for her, okay?

99
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:47,450
Good idea.

100
00:04:47,450 --> 00:04:48,420
Yes, let's go.

101
00:04:48,710 --> 00:04:49,810
I have some ingredients.

102
00:04:49,810 --> 00:04:50,530
So...

103
00:04:51,980 --> 00:04:52,940
Well...

104
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,390
It's okay.

105
00:04:56,390 --> 00:04:57,460
I'm okay.

106
00:04:59,830 --> 00:05:00,800
Is she really Xixi?

107
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,880
Yes.

108
00:05:02,220 --> 00:05:05,020
How long does she usually take
to get ready before going out?

109
00:05:05,020 --> 00:05:06,960
[Stairway Corner Ice]

110
00:05:11,860 --> 00:05:12,960
That's odd.

111
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,110
There is internet.

112
00:05:24,890 --> 00:05:26,690
He hasn't contacted me for days,

113
00:05:27,730 --> 00:05:29,990
and he hasn't come for shaved ice either.

114
00:05:43,050 --> 00:05:44,860
I thought my phone was broken.

115
00:05:46,909 --> 00:05:48,740
What are you thinking?

116
00:05:49,380 --> 00:05:50,710
Is your phone broken,

117
00:05:50,710 --> 00:05:51,780
or is it your brain?

118
00:05:51,970 --> 00:05:53,690
You've been playing with your phone
all morning,

119
00:05:53,690 --> 00:05:54,620
you know?

120
00:05:54,650 --> 00:05:55,850
I'm not playing.

121
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,960
I think there's no signal.

122
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:00,050
No signal? Let me see.

123
00:06:01,990 --> 00:06:03,690
The signal is great, full bars!

124
00:06:03,690 --> 00:06:05,030
Okay, I got it.

125
00:06:06,850 --> 00:06:08,580
Who's call are you waiting for?

126
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:09,900
I'm not waiting for anyone's call

127
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:11,270
or message.

128
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:15,170
Didn't I tell you

129
00:06:15,210 --> 00:06:16,060
that

130
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:19,040
you can't just wait
and expect customers to come

131
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:21,410
but look for customers.

132
00:06:22,110 --> 00:06:22,780
And this

133
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:24,310
also applies to

134
00:06:24,310 --> 00:06:25,280
other situations.

135
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:27,080
You should take the initiative.

136
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:27,810
Understand?

137
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:30,200
Did you take the initiative?

138
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:33,690
Every time Xiaohai comes over,

139
00:06:33,690 --> 00:06:34,790
I always greet him warmly

140
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:35,820
and friendly,

141
00:06:35,820 --> 00:06:36,290
right?

142
00:06:36,290 --> 00:06:37,830
Right.

143
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:40,060
He hasn't come

144
00:06:40,060 --> 00:06:41,400
for days, right?

145
00:06:42,230 --> 00:06:43,200
Who cares?

146
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,570
It's not my business.

147
00:06:46,330 --> 00:06:47,500
I see.

148
00:06:48,310 --> 00:06:49,440
Did you have a fight?

149
00:06:50,409 --> 00:06:51,510
Stop...

150
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:52,470
Stop gossiping!

151
00:06:52,470 --> 00:06:53,270
Just do your own things.

152
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:55,240
I'm already busy!

153
00:07:07,490 --> 00:07:09,160
It was me.

154
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:11,590
I know.

155
00:07:13,130 --> 00:07:14,960
Your phone is not broken,

156
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:17,030
but the tapioca pearls are going bad.
Hurry up!

157
00:07:17,030 --> 00:07:18,070
Okay.

158
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:20,130
I'm going bad too!

159
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:34,080
Only He Xiangyong knows
I drink bitter gourd black tea

160
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:35,380
when I'm stuck.

161
00:07:35,380 --> 00:07:36,310
How did you know?

162
00:07:36,409 --> 00:07:37,510
Really?

163
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:42,180
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

164
00:07:43,460 --> 00:07:45,830
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

165
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:47,730
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

166
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:49,760
What caterpillar?

167
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:53,600
You're still up?

168
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:55,590
Reading.

169
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:03,330
Did you put it there?

170
00:09:03,330 --> 00:09:04,670
Oh, it's my collection.

171
00:09:04,730 --> 00:09:05,830
Why is it there?

172
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:16,930
Aren't you scared?

173
00:09:16,930 --> 00:09:18,730
Why should I fear a caterpillar?

174
00:09:20,430 --> 00:09:22,230
Remember to turn off the lights.

175
00:09:32,740 --> 00:09:34,240
Why are you trembling?

176
00:09:36,190 --> 00:09:38,010
I just took a cold shower.

177
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:16,040
It's fake.

178
00:10:16,830 --> 00:10:17,890
It's not real.

179
00:10:24,610 --> 00:10:25,540
You've got this.

180
00:10:28,820 --> 00:10:29,780
It's fake.

181
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:31,700
It's not scary at all.

182
00:10:34,980 --> 00:10:36,580
But Chen Haowei is really...

183
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:39,040
really troublesome.

184
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:42,460
I'm such an idiot.

185
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:44,100
What am I thinking?

186
00:10:45,090 --> 00:10:46,950
How could they be the same person?

187
00:10:52,070 --> 00:10:53,400
Watch the stairs.

188
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:10,560
Welcome to Xingpu Island.

189
00:11:10,590 --> 00:11:12,330
Wish you have a good time.

190
00:11:26,210 --> 00:11:27,610
Did you forget anything?

191
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,520
"A Promise Beyond Time."

192
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,320
What promise?

193
00:11:34,810 --> 00:11:37,920
The publisher likes
straightforward titles,

194
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,980
but my managing editor and I

195
00:11:40,010 --> 00:11:42,210
prefer the one we came up with together,

196
00:11:42,850 --> 00:11:46,220
"Desserts, Seeds, and the Prophecy Diary."

197
00:11:46,250 --> 00:11:47,310
She's very famous.

198
00:11:47,370 --> 00:11:48,770
She has a lot of great works,

199
00:11:48,770 --> 00:11:50,500
like "The Hunter's Gentle Vacation,"

200
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:52,170
"Desserts, Seeds, and the Prophecy Diary,"
and "Goddess of Zandir."

201
00:11:52,170 --> 00:11:53,630
I love reading her comics.

202
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:55,340
Y-You're my idol.

203
00:12:02,970 --> 00:12:04,210
You're He Xiangyong, right?

204
00:12:04,210 --> 00:12:05,080
Yes.

205
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:05,960
No!

206
00:12:07,150 --> 00:12:08,820
I'm his friend.

207
00:12:09,290 --> 00:12:10,490
He once told me about

208
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:12,120
the book you just mentioned.

209
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:13,040
I heard they sell well.

210
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:14,100
Congratulations.

211
00:12:16,180 --> 00:12:18,030
No matter how someone's
appearance changes,

212
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:19,630
their soul remains the same.

213
00:12:20,470 --> 00:12:22,730
As you know,
I care about my privacy a lot.

214
00:12:22,890 --> 00:12:25,220
I'd never tell others about these things.

215
00:12:29,810 --> 00:12:31,350
What happened to you?

216
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,180
Why do you look different?

217
00:12:55,270 --> 00:12:57,140
I don't know how to explain.

218
00:12:57,990 --> 00:12:58,860
But

219
00:12:59,270 --> 00:13:02,870
do you believe that shooting stars
can make our wishes come true?

220
00:13:03,630 --> 00:13:04,970
Interesting.

221
00:13:05,830 --> 00:13:07,070
I want to hear it.

222
00:13:07,950 --> 00:13:10,680
Anyway, I made a wish,

223
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:12,560
and it really came true.

224
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:13,900
The next day,

225
00:13:13,930 --> 00:13:15,600
no one recognized me.

226
00:13:15,990 --> 00:13:18,190
I'm also trying to figure out what to do.

227
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:20,240
So,

228
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:22,350
you can't change back?

229
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:25,130
Have I changed?

230
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:27,940
I think I'm still the same person
I used to be.

231
00:13:28,890 --> 00:13:31,620
What was I like
when I was in the publishing house?

232
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:38,760
By the way, how did you recognize me?

233
00:13:46,790 --> 00:13:47,670
The gift.

234
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,520
Thanks.

235
00:13:52,460 --> 00:13:53,660
Thank you.

236
00:13:56,250 --> 00:13:58,220
I don't like socializing.

237
00:13:58,780 --> 00:14:00,750
Being my managing editor is hard,

238
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:03,520
but you've never complained.

239
00:14:05,390 --> 00:14:08,130
You're just like Xingpu Island,

240
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:11,230
full of energy and warmth.

241
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,530
More people should know about
Xingpu Island.

242
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,050
And you,

243
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,440
He Xiangyong,

244
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,870
also deserve to be seen.

245
00:14:29,890 --> 00:14:31,160
Stop here.

246
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:33,680
Goodbye.

247
00:14:54,770 --> 00:14:59,150
[Only when you embrace the broken pieces
can you become a better person]

248
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:19,940
Zhong

249
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:22,140
Have you seen Xiaohai lately?

250
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:23,000
Who?

251
00:15:23,230 --> 00:15:24,060
Xiaohai.

252
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,620
Have you seen him these days?

253
00:15:25,620 --> 00:15:27,690
He took leave several days ago
and hasn't come back.

254
00:15:27,690 --> 00:15:28,950
I need to find someone.

255
00:15:32,610 --> 00:15:33,910
Took leave?

256
00:15:36,030 --> 00:15:37,230
How's that possible?

257
00:15:49,340 --> 00:15:50,160
Mr. De,

258
00:15:50,540 --> 00:15:51,940
we're here for the beers.

259
00:15:52,550 --> 00:15:53,310
Xiangyong.

260
00:15:53,660 --> 00:15:54,560
Xiangyong.

261
00:15:54,710 --> 00:15:55,720
Have some candies.

262
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:57,580
Your favorite watermelon candy.

263
00:16:02,640 --> 00:16:03,570
Hong,

264
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:05,780
you've mistaken me for someone else.

265
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:16,550
Hong.

266
00:16:17,740 --> 00:16:19,740
Do you also think he's He Xiangyong?

267
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:23,100
Plum candy.

268
00:16:23,380 --> 00:16:24,110
Take it.

269
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:24,910
No need.

270
00:16:24,910 --> 00:16:25,960
Answer my question.

271
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:28,220
You also think he's He Xiangyong, right?

272
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:32,690
Thanks, Hong.

273
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:42,330
The shooting stars in Xingpu Island
are very beautiful, right?

274
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:45,480
They have magic.

275
00:16:46,020 --> 00:16:48,020
They can make your wishes come true.

276
00:16:50,770 --> 00:16:52,910
Do you know what will happen

277
00:16:53,910 --> 00:16:55,150
after that?

278
00:16:59,650 --> 00:17:00,750
The person will...

279
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:10,569
But love will remain.

280
00:17:10,890 --> 00:17:12,290
No watermelon candy?

281
00:17:24,599 --> 00:17:25,630
Thanks, ma'am.

282
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:26,540
Thanks.

283
00:17:26,569 --> 00:17:27,740
See you next time!

284
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:33,450
Hey, Mr. Li.

285
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:35,350
What big business
have you been dealing with?

286
00:17:35,350 --> 00:17:36,810
I haven't seen you all day.

287
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:38,880
No business. Someone went missing.

288
00:17:39,420 --> 00:17:39,920
I can't find him.

289
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:43,060
Missing? Then you should call the police.

290
00:17:43,660 --> 00:17:44,260
I...

291
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:45,560
What if...

292
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:47,260
What if he doesn't want to see me?

293
00:17:47,260 --> 00:17:48,590
I'll be so embarrassed.

294
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,760
So annoying. It's annoying when he comes,

295
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:52,900
and it's more annoying
when he doesn't show up.

296
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:54,230
Well, if you have a choice,

297
00:17:54,230 --> 00:17:55,640
will you see him

298
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:56,970
or not?

299
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:58,560
Of course I want to see him.

300
00:17:58,910 --> 00:17:59,770
Congratulations.

301
00:17:59,770 --> 00:18:00,670
You like him.

302
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:02,140
No way!

303
00:18:02,140 --> 00:18:03,040
I'd never like Hama-chan!

304
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:03,610
No way!

305
00:18:04,230 --> 00:18:05,630
Hama-chan...

306
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:08,530
You two aren't fighting,

307
00:18:08,550 --> 00:18:10,680
just being stubborn and moody.

308
00:18:11,950 --> 00:18:13,120
Mom, you misunderstood.

309
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:14,560
I want to see him

310
00:18:14,950 --> 00:18:16,270
because I want to beat him up.

311
00:18:16,270 --> 00:18:17,430
I don't like him.

312
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:18,960
Fine, go beat him up.

313
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:20,430
He's waiting for you at home.

314
00:18:20,430 --> 00:18:21,760
Here's your shaved ice
with green beans and tapioca pearls.

315
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:22,460
He's back.

316
00:18:22,930 --> 00:18:24,400
Hamaguchi Aomi,

317
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,870
I'll beat you up!

318
00:18:29,970 --> 00:18:31,040
Hamaguchi Aomi!

319
00:18:33,380 --> 00:18:34,670
Hamaguchi Aomi

320
00:18:34,950 --> 00:18:36,240
Yes!

321
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:38,170
Welcome!

322
00:18:38,310 --> 00:18:40,490
Have a seat.

323
00:18:41,390 --> 00:18:42,190
Here.

324
00:18:43,220 --> 00:18:43,870
Sit down.

325
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:50,120
charcoal-grilled sandwich
from Yancheng District, Kaohsiung,

326
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:51,590
squid roll rice noodles
from Guohua Street, Tainan,

327
00:18:51,590 --> 00:18:53,230
white vinegar cold noodles
from Wenhua Road, Chiayi,

328
00:18:53,230 --> 00:18:54,460
oyster fritter from Wanggong Fishing Port,
Changhua,

329
00:18:54,460 --> 00:18:55,760
jute leaf soup
from the Taichung Second Market,

330
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,100
Popiah from Hsinchu City God Temple,

331
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:59,260
and pork knuckle rice from Siping Street,
New Taipei.

332
00:18:59,260 --> 00:19:01,230
These are all your favorites.

333
00:19:02,790 --> 00:19:04,670
Are you crazy? You bought all of them?

334
00:19:04,670 --> 00:19:06,500
I didn't buy all of them.

335
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,330
I also made some.

336
00:19:09,360 --> 00:19:10,630
The jute leaf soup

337
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:11,590
was sold out,

338
00:19:11,610 --> 00:19:12,800
so I begged the shopkeeper

339
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:15,170
to sell me the ingredients,

340
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:17,030
and then I made it myself.

341
00:19:17,670 --> 00:19:18,550
Eat up.

342
00:19:21,820 --> 00:19:23,960
This is why you took leave these days?

343
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:26,010
How did you know?

344
00:19:26,130 --> 00:19:27,730
So, you care about me, right?

345
00:19:27,780 --> 00:19:28,910
I don't.

346
00:19:28,930 --> 00:19:30,710
I've never seen someone so heartless.

347
00:19:30,710 --> 00:19:31,820
You just vanished.

348
00:19:32,330 --> 00:19:33,230
You went to buy food,

349
00:19:33,230 --> 00:19:35,160
not like falling into a black hole.

350
00:19:35,220 --> 00:19:36,250
I'm sorry.

351
00:19:37,870 --> 00:19:39,600
There were many cities to go to,

352
00:19:39,850 --> 00:19:41,380
and the schedule was tight.

353
00:19:41,570 --> 00:19:42,630
Most importantly,

354
00:19:43,230 --> 00:19:45,430
I wanted to surprise you.

355
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:48,500
Try it.

356
00:19:51,310 --> 00:19:53,270
Is it good?

357
00:19:54,310 --> 00:19:55,010
It's good.

358
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:56,270
Okay!

359
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:02,070
[I like you.]

360
00:20:05,230 --> 00:20:06,210
[I like you.]

361
00:20:14,620 --> 00:20:15,720
You...

362
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:18,020
I was trying to stump you.

363
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:19,700
Why did you take it seriously?

364
00:20:23,990 --> 00:20:25,230
Whatever you want

365
00:20:25,250 --> 00:20:25,980
to drink

366
00:20:26,010 --> 00:20:26,710
or eat,

367
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:27,720
or wherever you want to go,

368
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:28,740
just ring this bell,

369
00:20:28,740 --> 00:20:30,570
and I'll show up immediately!

370
00:20:31,330 --> 00:20:32,230
Here.

371
00:20:34,660 --> 00:20:36,060
As long as it's about you,

372
00:20:36,230 --> 00:20:38,440
I'll try my best!

373
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:41,940
Idiot.

374
00:20:42,790 --> 00:20:43,490
Then...

375
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:45,820
Did I pass the test?

376
00:20:48,970 --> 00:20:49,910
You missed
Black Bamboo Chicken Feet Jelly,

377
00:20:49,910 --> 00:20:50,780
stinky tofu from Heping Road,

378
00:20:50,780 --> 00:20:52,910
and garlic pork thick soup
from Taishan Road, Yilan.

379
00:20:52,910 --> 00:20:54,520
Sorry.

380
00:20:54,930 --> 00:20:56,460
I'll make it up right away.

381
00:20:57,710 --> 00:20:59,180
What's wrong with you?

382
00:21:07,150 --> 00:21:07,810
Yes!

383
00:21:08,290 --> 00:21:09,490
How can I help you?

384
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:12,230
Oh, water! No problem.

385
00:21:12,930 --> 00:21:14,100
Hurry up. I'm choking.

386
00:21:14,100 --> 00:21:14,730
Okay.

387
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:15,720
Sorry.

388
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:16,850
Have some water.

389
00:21:18,710 --> 00:21:19,570
Thank you, sir.

390
00:21:25,180 --> 00:21:26,480
Anyone here?

391
00:21:27,170 --> 00:21:28,160
Hello.

392
00:21:28,310 --> 00:21:29,070
Wait a minute.

393
00:21:29,070 --> 00:21:29,840
Okay.

394
00:21:29,890 --> 00:21:30,920
-Hello.
-Hello.

395
00:21:30,970 --> 00:21:31,570
Mr. Jin?

396
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:32,300
Yes.

397
00:21:32,350 --> 00:21:33,850
I need to check your ID.

398
00:21:33,850 --> 00:21:34,920
Okay.

399
00:21:37,080 --> 00:21:37,980
Thanks.

400
00:21:38,010 --> 00:21:39,780
You can take a look around.

401
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:50,640
Chen Haowei.

402
00:21:50,660 --> 00:21:51,930
Why are there guests?

403
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:52,900
I invited them.

404
00:21:53,030 --> 00:21:53,960
What's wrong?

405
00:21:54,140 --> 00:21:55,340
Didn't you see my note?

406
00:21:55,340 --> 00:21:56,040
There's a fishing group coming,

407
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:57,770
so we can't take any new guests.

408
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:58,940
What note?

409
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:01,650
Where's my note?

410
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:02,900
What note?

411
00:22:02,930 --> 00:22:04,170
My sticky note.

412
00:22:04,710 --> 00:22:05,770
Why can't I find it?

413
00:22:09,380 --> 00:22:10,460
Where is it?

414
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:15,950
It's here.

415
00:22:15,980 --> 00:22:17,050
It fell down.

416
00:22:19,630 --> 00:22:21,270
Honey, you're so good at picking places.

417
00:22:21,270 --> 00:22:22,980
That's why I booked it.

418
00:22:23,010 --> 00:22:24,810
Mr. Jin, Mrs. Jin.

419
00:22:24,830 --> 00:22:26,200
Yes.

420
00:22:26,230 --> 00:22:27,100
I'm so sorry.

421
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:28,720
We made a mistake.

422
00:22:28,750 --> 00:22:31,460
We're fully booked today.

423
00:22:31,550 --> 00:22:32,380
What does that mean?

424
00:22:32,380 --> 00:22:34,280
We can't check in now?

425
00:22:34,550 --> 00:22:35,680
We booked it a long time ago.

426
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:36,520
What do you mean by fully booked?

427
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:37,630
Why can't we stay...

428
00:22:37,630 --> 00:22:38,150
Actually, you can.

429
00:22:38,150 --> 00:22:39,240
But we booked it a long time ago.

430
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:39,800
You can.

431
00:22:39,820 --> 00:22:41,090
Wait a minute.

432
00:22:42,510 --> 00:22:44,080
I checked with him.

433
00:22:44,100 --> 00:22:45,630
I called him,

434
00:22:45,660 --> 00:22:47,000
and he said yes.

435
00:22:47,030 --> 00:22:48,700
Then where should we go?

436
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:50,720
Let me contact
our friendly guesthouse for you.

437
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:51,850
They must have rooms.

438
00:22:51,850 --> 00:22:52,780
Wait a minute.

439
00:22:52,810 --> 00:22:54,980
But we want to stay here.

440
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:55,700
Sorry.

441
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:57,410
[Guest, Mr. Lin]

442
00:22:55,730 --> 00:22:57,270
We're fully booked today.

443
00:22:58,070 --> 00:22:59,140
But we booked it a long time ago.

444
00:22:59,140 --> 00:23:00,670
Hello, Auntie Jiao.

445
00:23:00,670 --> 00:23:02,440
This is Where Is My Home. I'm Xiaoyou.

446
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:03,780
Do you have an empty room?

447
00:23:03,780 --> 00:23:05,410
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

448
00:23:05,820 --> 00:23:06,480
Great.

449
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:07,150
We have two guests...

450
00:23:07,150 --> 00:23:08,010
Aren't you a top student?

451
00:23:08,010 --> 00:23:10,080
How could you make such a stupid mistake?

452
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:11,390
Just use Mr. Lin's money.

453
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:13,120
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

454
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:14,780
Chen Haowei, my money!

455
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:16,790
You're supposed to be responsible!

456
00:23:16,790 --> 00:23:17,620
We've been looking forward to it!

457
00:23:17,620 --> 00:23:19,030
We booked it a long time ago!

458
00:23:19,030 --> 00:23:20,360
Chen Haowei.

459
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:20,860
Yes.

460
00:23:20,860 --> 00:23:22,000
Didn't you see my note?

461
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,460
There's a fishing group coming,
so we can't take any new guests.

462
00:23:23,460 --> 00:23:24,600
Go 50 meters straight,

463
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:26,400
then you'll see a yellow sign on the left.

464
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:27,670
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

465
00:23:36,360 --> 00:23:37,460
It's settled.

466
00:23:38,900 --> 00:23:40,000
Chen Haowei.

467
00:23:40,740 --> 00:23:41,870
Chen Haowei, where are you going?

468
00:23:41,870 --> 00:23:43,130
Chen Haowei, where...

469
00:23:49,090 --> 00:23:50,190
Chen Haowei.

470
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:39,560
Chen Haowei!

471
00:24:41,690 --> 00:24:42,480
Chen Haowei!

472
00:24:42,970 --> 00:24:43,540
Chen Haowei!

473
00:24:43,540 --> 00:24:44,470
Stop running!

474
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:46,280
Where are you going?

475
00:25:00,620 --> 00:25:02,220
Chen Haowei!

476
00:25:05,010 --> 00:25:06,280
Chen Haowei!

477
00:26:13,560 --> 00:26:15,090
I'll tell Mr. He

478
00:26:15,900 --> 00:26:17,830
I'll be responsible for the loss.

479
00:26:18,670 --> 00:26:19,670
No need.

480
00:26:19,990 --> 00:26:21,560
You didn't mean to do this.

481
00:26:21,890 --> 00:26:23,490
We'll shoulder it together.

482
00:26:26,170 --> 00:26:28,510
I'll bear my own mistakes.

483
00:26:29,060 --> 00:26:30,260
This is my principle.

484
00:26:33,580 --> 00:26:34,310
Fine.

485
00:26:35,540 --> 00:26:37,760
You should take a day off tomorrow.

486
00:26:41,620 --> 00:26:42,650
Stop smiling.

487
00:26:45,970 --> 00:26:47,570
It's okay to be sad.

488
00:26:48,700 --> 00:26:50,500
You don't have to keep smiling.

489
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:57,060
I'm really fine.

490
00:27:04,110 --> 00:27:05,110
Let's go to sleep.

491
00:27:34,450 --> 00:27:35,320
By the way,

492
00:27:35,850 --> 00:27:37,680
why did you run away?

493
00:27:40,850 --> 00:27:42,260
Actually,

494
00:27:44,860 --> 00:27:46,190
I have a panic disorder.

495
00:27:53,520 --> 00:27:55,720
You're just pushing yourself too hard.

496
00:27:59,840 --> 00:28:00,670
But

497
00:28:01,170 --> 00:28:02,240
I didn't expect

498
00:28:03,240 --> 00:28:05,750
you'd carry so much burden,

499
00:28:07,380 --> 00:28:10,510
because you've always been so optimistic
in front of us.

500
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:21,390
I thought my life was miserable.

501
00:28:23,060 --> 00:28:24,760
But after listening to your story,

502
00:28:24,760 --> 00:28:26,600
I think I'm lucky.

503
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:32,660
However,

504
00:28:33,010 --> 00:28:34,880
is there any other way

505
00:28:35,510 --> 00:28:38,440
to deal with your symptoms
besides taking medicine?

506
00:28:39,500 --> 00:28:40,370
Running.

507
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:43,920
I don't think about those things
when I run.

508
00:28:47,370 --> 00:28:48,870
What if you get a cramp?

509
00:28:52,710 --> 00:28:53,980
Are you serious?

510
00:28:54,770 --> 00:28:55,560
I'm talking about

511
00:28:55,560 --> 00:28:57,220
something painful in my life.

512
00:28:57,540 --> 00:28:58,330
Do you realize

513
00:28:58,330 --> 00:28:59,700
what you're saying?

514
00:29:00,330 --> 00:29:01,030
Alright.

515
00:29:01,170 --> 00:29:02,700
Let me tell you another one.

516
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:03,490
Listen,

517
00:29:03,550 --> 00:29:04,880
when I was working,

518
00:29:05,340 --> 00:29:06,540
there was a colleague

519
00:29:07,030 --> 00:29:08,770
who would cry every single day.

520
00:29:09,310 --> 00:29:11,750
I felt so sorry for him.

521
00:29:12,210 --> 00:29:13,350
Eventually, I'd put

522
00:29:13,350 --> 00:29:15,680
a box of tissues

523
00:29:15,910 --> 00:29:17,240
wherever he might go.

524
00:29:20,600 --> 00:29:21,670
Was he depressed?

525
00:29:21,740 --> 00:29:22,310
Yes.

526
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:26,910
I have a panic disorder.
I'm not depressed.

527
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:29,840
That's right.

528
00:29:31,300 --> 00:29:32,180
Listen,

529
00:29:32,820 --> 00:29:35,020
depression is a constant low mood,

530
00:29:35,260 --> 00:29:37,500
whereas panic disorder just hits you
all of a sudden.

531
00:29:37,500 --> 00:29:38,760
Do you understand now?

532
00:29:39,610 --> 00:29:40,370
Got it.

533
00:29:41,210 --> 00:29:42,080
So,

534
00:29:42,110 --> 00:29:44,170
don't stop me when you see me running.

535
00:29:45,300 --> 00:29:47,400
But you almost ran into the sea today.

536
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:50,260
I was going to turn back!

537
00:29:51,350 --> 00:29:52,020
Forget it.

538
00:29:52,090 --> 00:29:53,120
I shouldn't have told you.

539
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:53,960
Alright.

540
00:29:54,350 --> 00:29:55,050
Then

541
00:29:55,050 --> 00:29:56,580
let's not talk about this.

542
00:29:56,780 --> 00:29:58,350
Maybe I can tell you a joke.

543
00:29:59,480 --> 00:30:02,650
Do you know why guards

544
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:03,940
are always chuckling?

545
00:30:04,220 --> 00:30:05,000
Why?

546
00:30:05,580 --> 00:30:08,580
They're standing at
the chuckling (checking) point.

547
00:30:09,790 --> 00:30:11,160
It's not funny.

548
00:30:12,540 --> 00:30:13,440
Listen,

549
00:30:14,210 --> 00:30:15,110
Judy,

550
00:30:15,780 --> 00:30:18,440
what illness does Judy get
if she works too hard?

551
00:30:19,380 --> 00:30:20,380
Overwork?

552
00:30:22,080 --> 00:30:24,040
Jaundice (Judy's) disease.

553
00:30:24,320 --> 00:30:25,890
Let me tell you a joke.

554
00:30:27,030 --> 00:30:29,830
One day, Xiaoming and Xiaohua
were riding horses.

555
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:32,370
Halfway through, Xiaoming shouted,

556
00:30:32,390 --> 00:30:33,630
"Rein in! Rein in!"

557
00:30:34,520 --> 00:30:35,990
Then Xiaohua said,

558
00:30:36,100 --> 00:30:38,050
"It's not raining."

559
00:30:38,070 --> 00:30:39,610
Then he fell off the cliff.

560
00:30:42,730 --> 00:30:44,030
Isn't it funny?

561
00:30:44,060 --> 00:30:48,800
Why do penguins always look so smart?

562
00:30:48,830 --> 00:30:50,400
Why do they

563
00:30:51,490 --> 00:30:52,360
look so smart?

564
00:30:52,380 --> 00:30:53,670
Because

565
00:30:53,850 --> 00:30:55,580
they're always wearing suits.

566
00:30:56,390 --> 00:30:57,520
What a bad joke!

567
00:30:57,900 --> 00:30:59,860
Do you know the color of toilet paper?

568
00:30:59,860 --> 00:31:01,590
Why did the phone go to therapy?

569
00:31:01,620 --> 00:31:02,370
Depressed?

570
00:31:03,870 --> 00:31:05,020
Because it had

571
00:31:05,610 --> 00:31:07,750
too many hang-ups.

572
00:31:14,770 --> 00:31:16,170
He!

573
00:31:33,310 --> 00:31:34,410
He!

574
00:31:54,780 --> 00:31:56,020
Chen Haowei.

575
00:31:56,430 --> 00:31:58,100
Turn off the alarm.

576
00:32:02,550 --> 00:32:03,820
Sorry, it's mine.

577
00:32:04,670 --> 00:32:05,540
Well...

578
00:32:05,950 --> 00:32:06,720
Sorry to bother you.

579
00:32:06,720 --> 00:32:07,920
Have you seen Mr. He?

580
00:32:11,070 --> 00:32:13,510
You just woke up. How could you see him?

581
00:32:13,850 --> 00:32:15,050
I'll look for him.

582
00:32:15,090 --> 00:32:16,200
Wait, Uncle Hua.

583
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:16,900
It's okay.

584
00:32:16,900 --> 00:32:17,700
It's not what you think.

585
00:32:17,700 --> 00:32:18,970
I know what happened.

586
00:32:18,970 --> 00:32:20,430
Maybe it was too cold last night.

587
00:32:20,430 --> 00:32:21,460
Be careful.

588
00:32:21,940 --> 00:32:22,770
I never came.

589
00:32:22,770 --> 00:32:23,500
Bye.

590
00:32:33,300 --> 00:32:34,970
I'll brush my teeth.

591
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:55,300
I've been looking for you.

592
00:32:55,690 --> 00:32:57,090
Why did you drink so much?

593
00:33:01,470 --> 00:33:03,800
Didn't you go to the main island
to find your son?

594
00:33:03,800 --> 00:33:05,260
Did you have a fight again?

595
00:33:13,430 --> 00:33:15,910
If he knew I made a decision,

596
00:33:16,700 --> 00:33:19,100
he'd come back to quarrel with me.

597
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:22,090
What decision?

598
00:33:23,460 --> 00:33:24,070
Tell me.

599
00:33:28,020 --> 00:33:29,660
I'm going to sell my house.

600
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:40,830
[Epilogue]

601
00:33:57,870 --> 00:33:59,430
I'm bad at playing basketball.

602
00:33:59,430 --> 00:34:00,890
I always lose.

603
00:34:03,520 --> 00:34:05,050
I was lucky this time.

604
00:34:05,430 --> 00:34:06,960
Maybe you'll win next time.

605
00:34:07,530 --> 00:34:10,620
Having fun is all that matters
when playing with friends.

606
00:34:10,620 --> 00:34:12,350
Winning is not that important.

607
00:34:13,940 --> 00:34:15,170
You're right.

608
00:34:17,830 --> 00:34:18,940
Besides,

609
00:34:19,340 --> 00:34:20,500
your hands

610
00:34:21,880 --> 00:34:24,010
aren't meant for playing basketball.

611
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:31,909
You have a pair of Takehiko Inoue's hands.

612
00:34:37,420 --> 00:34:38,650
Give me a hand.

613
00:34:38,679 --> 00:34:39,949
Okay, wait for me.

614
00:34:39,969 --> 00:34:40,690
Let's go.

615
00:34:43,210 --> 00:34:44,280
Hurry up.

616
00:34:50,219 --> 00:34:51,280
Chen Haowei!

617
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:52,790
I forgot something.

618
00:34:52,810 --> 00:34:53,550
What did you forget?

619
00:34:53,550 --> 00:34:54,350
I can help you.

620
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:56,110
It's okay. No need.

621
00:34:57,420 --> 00:34:58,950
I'll go back to get it, okay?

622
00:34:59,860 --> 00:35:00,890
Caterpillar?

623
00:35:01,390 --> 00:35:03,190
Are you afraid of caterpillars?

624
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:04,560
What caterpillar?

625
00:35:04,560 --> 00:35:05,820
Look at the cockroach!

626
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:08,010
Why did you lie to me?

627
00:35:33,330 --> 00:35:34,390
I need to pay 5 million TWD?

628
00:35:33,730 --> 00:35:38,000
[Next Episode]

629
00:35:34,790 --> 00:35:35,560
Sir.

630
00:35:35,930 --> 00:35:37,660
Sorry, I'm the president.

631
00:35:37,660 --> 00:35:39,230
Take a photo of this dangerous building

632
00:35:39,230 --> 00:35:40,670
and see if there's any place to change.

633
00:35:40,670 --> 00:35:42,200
Do you know this is an ancient relic?

634
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:44,240
You know nothing, huh?

635
00:35:44,240 --> 00:35:46,830
I don't think you should
invest in real estate.

636
00:35:46,830 --> 00:35:48,060
I finally found you.

637
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:49,630
I won't let you go this time!

638
00:35:50,140 --> 00:35:51,010
He Xiangyong!

